  <prompt>
    Resolve UQ-04 (concrete column layouts for sprk_kpiassessment + sprk_invoice Matter-context views) by interviewing the owner (Ralph) on which fields each savedquery should display. Then author two savedqueries in Dataverse: one for `sprk_kpiassessment` (Matter Health drill-through) and one for `sprk_invoice` (Budget Performance drill-through). Both filter by the current Matter ID (passed via URL params from VisualHost CardChrome).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer. Expert in Dataverse savedquery records, FetchXML query syntax, layoutXml, and parent-context filter parameter passing via Custom Page URL.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Two new savedquery records exist in Dataverse: `sprk_kpiassessment_matter_context_view` and `sprk_invoice_matter_context_view`. Both correctly filter by Matter ID parameter and render expected columns per Ralph's spec.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per FR-CON-01, FR-CON-02, UQ-04. The Matter Health drill-through dialog displays related KPI assessments for the current Matter (passed as `filterField=sprk_matter_lookup, filterValue={matterId}` URL params). Same pattern for Budget Performance → Invoices. The column list per view is a Ralph decision — interview him for: KPI view columns (likely: Name, Score, Status, Updated date) and Invoice view columns (likely: Number, Amount, Status, Due date, Paid date).
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>docs/guides/DATAVERSE-HOW-TO-CREATE-UPDATE-SCHEMA.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-datagrid-framework-r1/notes/drafts/020-savedquery-column-layouts.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="project">Both savedqueries MUST accept Matter ID as filter parameter via FetchXML `&lt;filter&gt;&lt;condition attribute='sprk_matter_lookup' operator='eq-userid' value='@MatterId'/&gt;&lt;/filter&gt;` pattern (or appropriate dynamic-value syntax).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">layoutXml must define column widths matching MDA OOB visual density.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">`statecode = 0` only (active records); `querytype = 0` (saved view).</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>docs/guides/DATAVERSE-HOW-TO-CREATE-UPDATE-SCHEMA.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/dataverse/web-api-client.md</file>
